<br>
In order to keep consistency between guilds we have created a Council. The Council was set up to ensure that if a member wishes to enter a new world as a Silver Hawk, they can do so knowing that the Silver Hawks are consistent throughout each gaming world.<br>
<br>
The functions and goals of the Council:<br>
* Create and maintain cohesion of the Silver Hawk guild.<br>
* Protect and communicate the Silver Hawk virtues to all those that are in the guild.<br>
* Discuss and share ideas for policy changes of specific guilds (if and when necessary).<br>
* Discuss and implement guild wide policies across all game worlds (as necessary).<br>
* Moderate the message board and website etc.<br>
* Facilitate future Silver Hawk guild establishment in other worlds.<br>
* Act as council to specific factions of the Silver Hawks.<br>
* Assist the officers and leaders in setting up and maintaining guild structures.<br>
<br>
The Council is made up of the following people:<br>
Hawkfeather - EQ guild leader and original founder of the Silver Hawks in EQ (Mith Marr) (Should he ever resurface)<br>
Darkarr – Long time EQ guild leader (Mith Marr &amp; Drinal), Magistrate in DAoC<br>
Quasimo – General in EQ, short time EQ guild leader, founder and former leader of DAoC Hawks<br>
Fernus - The Prophet - Future Guild Leader in Star Wars Galaxies<br>
Zamori - Long standing Silver Hawk, former co-guild leader in EQ <br>
Haydenpayne – Current EQ Guild Leader<br>
Tyza – Current DAoC Guild Leader<br>
<br>
We are passionate about this guild, about its ideals. We have fought each other and others to form what we have here today. We have been in just about every possible situation you can be in with a guild and we are still here. We have learned from past mistakes and forged forward and we hope the future leaders will be wise enough to tap into this resource. I cannot tell you how we would have killed for someone to be there to help us when things looked its worse, if even to just say &quot;Hold the line, everything will be all right.&quot; If we can continue to build upon the past we can keep tweaking this guild until it is perfect or as close to perfect as possible.<br>
<br>
Most of us in the council don't play in either world currently so that's why we need input from the current leaders to shape policy for consistency across the worlds, two and counting. And even though we don't pay our 12.95 a month &quot;due&quot; the time we have put into all of this should have us set for life I would hope. &lt;Thinks about the time put into the forums alone and shudders&gt; We volunteer to be here. We have one hope…to make the Silver Hawks a special place for all Hawks to have fun, make friends, and slay foes, whether they are current or future members.  <p>Tyza ThePrincess - Level 46 Warden<BR>Appalonia Knight - Level 25 Heroine<BR>Darkessa - Level 8 Rangerette<BR><BR>Proud Princess of the Silver Hawks and proud member of the Hibernian Coalition
